Tired of constantly tweaking work priorities every time a pawn levels up, has a mental break, or joins the colony? Don't want to manually assign priorities to temporary colonist ?

I made this mod because I wanted the Work tab to feel like something I could mostly ignore without losing control over my colony.

Instead of spending time micromanaging numbers, you can focus on actually playing the game (aka managing other more interesting numbers).

{{image:banner01-details}}

Adaptive Priorities automatically considers:[list]
[*] Current skill levels
[*] Passions
[*] Learning speed
[*] Inspirations
[*] Work urgency
[*] Ideoligion work preferences
[*] Pawns that become temporarily unavailable (downed, mental breaks, off-map, etc.)
[*] Related work stats (carry capacity and move speed for hauling, yield for mining, etc.)
[*] Your mechs and drones frees colonists from work automatons already handle.
[/list]

When a pawn can't perform their usual work, their responsibilities are redistributed to the rest of the colony.

On smaller colonies, the mod also makes sure every important work type has someone assigned, even if they're not the ideal candidate. Having a mediocre cook is usually better than having nobody cook at all.

By default, priorities are re-evaluated once every in-game hour. This can be configured to update less frequently depending on your preference.

{{image:banner02-middleclick}}

The entire mod is built around one idea: [b]be as unintrusive as possible.[/b]

Rather than add clutter with a new in-game UI full of options, Adaptive Priorities lets you override the automatic system directly from the vanilla Work tab.

You can lock assignments with a [b]simple middle mouse click[/b]:
[list]
[*] Lock an entire work type (column)
[*] Lock an individual priority
[*] Lock an entire pawn
[/list]

Locked entries are never modified by the automatic assignment.

{{image:banner03-ext-worker-awareness}}

Built a Lifter ? Cranked out a shed full of clankers ?

When your mechs and drones can cover a job, the mod will quietly pulls colonists off it and puts them on the work only [i]they[/i] can do. The pawns it frees are always the worst fits, so your best hauler keeps hauling and your ace crafters stays on bench for quality.
[list]
[*][b]"It just works"[/b]. Accounts for biotech's and any modded mechs dynamically.
[*]A dedicated settings tab lets you toggle on/off the feature and set each job to Off, Reduce (keep a backup of colonists), or Full offload.
[*]Safe by default: firefighting, doctoring and other emergency work is never thinned.
[/list]

[hr][/hr]

{{image:banner04-configuration}}

By design, the mod works out of the box with sane defaults.

If you want more control, the settings let you tune how much skills, passions, and work speed count, set each work type's importance, and adjust the bonus of every passion — modded ones included.
Every single option has a tooltip explaining what it does and what your current value means for your colony, anything you change can be reset with one click.

{{image:banner05-performance}}

Adaptive Priorities has very little performance impact during normal gameplay, even on colonies of 40+ pawns.

{{image:banner06-compat}}

[b]Modded Work Types[/b]: Works with virtually all modded work types out of the box using sensible derived defaults. Individual work types can be customized in the mod settings.
- [url=https://steamcommunity.com/sharedfiles/filedetails/?id=2900108163]Hunters Use Melee! (Continued)[/url]: Patched to correctly display the melee passion in the work tab. Melee is taken into account when computing hunt priorities.

[b]Modded Passions[/b]: Works with all modded passions. The mod derives sane defaults if there is no explicit mod integration.
- [url=https://steamcommunity.com/sharedfiles/filedetails/?id=3448953006]Alpha Skills[/url]: Fully supports Alpha Skills passions, including their unique behavior.
- [url=https://steamcommunity.com/sharedfiles/filedetails/?id=3400246558]Vanilla Skills Expanded[/url]: Fully supports Vanilla Skills Expanded passions.

[b]UI and Priority mods[/b]
- [url=https://steamcommunity.com/sharedfiles/filedetails/?id=3453549086]Fluffy's Work Tab Continued[/url]: Fully supported. (Including the 1-9 range) 
- [url=https://steamcommunity.com/sharedfiles/filedetails/?id=1994006442]Priority Master[/url]: Fully supported priority range of 1-99

[b]External workers[/b]
- [url=https://steamcommunity.com/workshop/filedetails/?id=3733951755]Vanilla Quests Expanded - Drone Factory[/url]: Fully supported, patches in the drones definition as they dont use vanilla mech Defs.
- [url=https://steamcommunity.com/workshop/filedetails/?id=2973169158]Alpha mechs[/url]: Fully supported

